-- Jeff Green Hits 3-Pointer at Buzzer as Celtics Top Heat 111-110
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-11-10T05:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-10/jeff-green-hits-3-pointer-at-buzzer-as-celtics-top-heat-111-110.html
Jeff Green  hit a 3-pointer at the
buzzer to give the Boston Celtics a 111-110 victory over the
defending National Basketball Association champion Miami Heat.  The Celtics recorded their third straight win last night
and improved to 3-4. The Heat fell to 4-3 after the loss at
AmericanAirlines Arena in Miami.  Green took a pass from  Gerald Wallace  and fired a shot over
LeBron James for the basket that was checked by video review
before the win was awarded.  Green had 24 points, Avery Bradley added 17 and Jordan Crawford scored 15 for the Celtics, who trailed 60-59 at the
half.  James had 25 points and 10 assists with Chris Bosh tallying
20 points and  Dwyane Wade  scoring 18 for Miami.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  